-- Genzyme Shares Advance Most in a Decade on Reports of Sanofi Buyout Offer
-- Elizabeth Lopatto
-- 2010-07-23T17:33:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/genzyme-shares-rise-most-since-1999-on-reports-of-sanofi-takeover-approach.html

          
          
             Genzyme Corp. shares increased the
most in more than a decade in New York trading on media reports
that Paris-based drugmaker Sanofi-Aventis SA made an offer to
acquire the company.  
 The shares rose $10.32, or 19 percent, to $64.19, at 1:30
p.m. in Nasdaq Stock Market composite trading. The unsolicited
offer for Cambridge, Massachusetts-based Genzyme was reported by
CNBC and the Wall Street Journal.  
